In Fig. 6
                        , the percent of green space within 1/4 km is shown for select EnviroAtlas featured communities. Areas with lower values for this indicator are shown in yellow and may be associated with neighborhoods that are more impervious, and potentially at risk for hazards like flooding and urban heat stress. Likewise, opportunities for health promotional activities such as outdoor physical fitness and social interactions may be decreased in areas with less green space. For these reasons, we believe this to be a good environmental indicator for examining spatial inequalities in areas that have had increased or decreased opportunities for inclusive, resilient, and sustainable urbanization. In the 2018 SDG Index and Dashboards Report, the only environmental indicator for SDG 11 included was annual mean concentration of particulate matter of <2.5 μm of diameter (PM

                           2.5

                        ) in urban areas (μg/m

                           3

                        ), and no indicators for 11.3 were reported (Sachs et al., 2018).
